case.name: First Act
case.description: Miku is the first to masturbate, and calls it a "Performance", in reference to the fact that she's a digital singer.

case.name: Time to Perform
case.description: Miku is about to masturbate, and calls it a "Performance", in reference to the fact that she's a digital singer.

case.name: Strip Poker But Nothing's Stripped
case.description: Miku Won the game, but didn't take anything off, and wonders if that defeats the purpose of the game.

case.name: Do I know you?
case.description: If Miku and Kizuna are playing the same game, Miku thinks she might regonize her.

case.name: Question for blue-hairs
case.description: If Miku is playing with anybody with blue hair, she'll ask how their hair got it's color.

case.name: Miku Day
case.description: On March 9th, Hatsune Miku will casually drop the fact that it's "Miku Day", but isn't entirely sure why it's celebrated.

case.name: After-Game Performance
case.description: If any other idols are playing with Miku, she will ask them about doing a performance after the game.

case.name: Sick of Streaming
case.description: If Streaming-Chan is playing with Miku, After at least 5 rounds, She will express her discomfort over Streaming-Chan's choice to stream the game online.

case.name: Sonic Suit
case.description: If Amy Rose is selected as an opponent, Miku will ask if she wants "That Sonic Costume She borrowed" back. This is in reference to an actual outfit worn by Miku in the Project Diva Games.

case.name: MoonInTrouble
case.description: When Playing with Bobobo, after his first strip stage, Miku will reference the fact that Moon also tried to do that, but that got her into trouble, so Miku asks why this guy is any different.

case.name: Digital Stripping
case.description: After Stripping off her shirt, Miku realizes that, since she's digital, she could easily get rid of her own clothes, but then reasons that it's less fun to do it that way.

case.name: A Digital Orgasm
case.description: After Finishing, Miku comments that she never thought a digital singer could orgasm the way the other characters do.

case.name: Harry Potter and Mincraft
case.description: Miku explains that some people say that she made Minecraft and wrote Harry Potter, but doesn't have a clue as to why that is.

case.name: Vegetable Juice
case.description: Miku talks about Vegetable Juice, and how it's her favorite thing to drink.

case.name: Performing Tips
case.description: Miku spouts out various tips for performing for a crowd.

case.name: Fellow Vocaloids
case.description: Miku talks about some of her Vocaloid friends.

case.name: Please Don't Record Me
case.description: If Streaming-Chan is in the game, When Miku is Masturbating, she hopes that Streaming-Chan isn't recording her.

case.name: Please Don't Play With Me Again
case.description: If Miku loses the game, she will her express hewr relief that the game is over, while also hoping that she doesn't have to play with Streaming-Chan ever again.

case.name: Fed Up With The Stream
case.description: If Streaming-Chan is in the game, after at least 10 rounds, Miku will go off on Streaming-Chan, though trails off. (You can infer what she plans to do with her here.)

case.name: Truly Digital?
case.description: After finishing, Miku reflects on the game, noting how she was able to do all the things a human would do.

case.name: Finally Cut Off The Camera
case.description: After finishing, if Miku is playing with Streaming-Chan, she'll hope that Streaming-Chan has finally cut her camera off.

case.name: My Fellow Idols
case.description: If Miku is playing with any other character with the "idol" tag, she'll ask how their recent performances have been?

case.name: After the Performace
case.description: After Finishing, Miku will ask any characters with the "idol" tag about what they like doing after a performance.

case.name: Love Songs
case.description: During the month of Feburary, Miku will ask the other players about their favorite love song.

case.name: I've got a game (On Switch)
case.description: If Miku is playing with anyone from a Nintendo Game, she'll comment that she recently had a game drop on the Switch.

case.name: Is he my brother?
case.description: When playing with the Girlfriend, Miku will tell her that some people think that her boyfriend is her brother, but she doesn't seem to understand why.

case.name: My Fellow Musicians
case.description: If Miku is playing with any other musicians (with the exception of Japanese Idols), Miku will ask them about the kinds of music they like performing the most.

case.name: I'm a Vocaloid
case.description: Miku brings up the fact that she's a Vocaloid to the other players.

case.name: Miku's Stockings
case.description: When an opponent is stripping their socks, Miku will bring up how important her stockings are to her outfit.

case.name: Asking about gloves
case.description: If the other opponent is stripping gloves, Miku will ask them why they chose to wear them.

case.name: Identifying name (ex. Hand=Bad)
case.description: Miku asks the other players if they've seen the papparazi around, as she fears that they might be chasing her down.
